1
00:00:08,416 --> 00:00:13,375
♪

2
00:00:21,416 --> 00:00:24,333
♪ Here he comes,
here comes Speed Racer ♪

3
00:00:24,416 --> 00:00:27,750
♪ He's a demon on wheels ♪

4
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:31,791
♪ He's a demon and he's gonna
be chasing after someone ♪

5
00:00:33,916 --> 00:00:36,875
♪ He's gaining on you
so you better look alive ♪

6
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:40,166
♪ He's busy revving up
the powerful Mach 5 ♪

7
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:42,500
♪ And when the odds
are against him ♪

8
00:00:42,583 --> 00:00:46,458
♪ And there's dangerous
work to do ♪

9
00:00:46,541 --> 00:00:52,333
♪ You bet your life Speed Racer
will see it through ♪

10
00:00:52,416 --> 00:00:55,375
♪ Go, Speed Racer
Go, Speed Racer ♪

11
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:58,541
♪ Go, Speed Racer, go! ♪

12
00:00:58,625 --> 00:01:01,583
♪ He's off and flying as he
guns the car around the track ♪

13
00:01:01,666 --> 00:01:04,666
♪ He's jamming down the pedal
like he's never coming back ♪

14
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:07,791
♪ Adventure's waiting
just ahead ♪

15
00:01:07,875 --> 00:01:10,875
♪ Go, Speed Racer
Go, Speed Racer ♪

16
00:01:10,958 --> 00:01:15,208
♪ Go, Speed Racer, go! ♪

17
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:24,083
[SPEED]
The controls on the Mach 5--

18
00:01:24,166 --> 00:01:27,375
the amazing car designed
and built by my father.

19
00:01:27,458 --> 00:01:30,375
Control Button A:
releases powerful jacks

20
00:01:30,458 --> 00:01:32,625
which boost the car so that
our mechanic, Sparky,

21
00:01:32,708 --> 00:01:35,833
can make repairs
and adjustments.

22
00:01:35,916 --> 00:01:37,833
Control B: When this
button is pressed,

23
00:01:37,916 --> 00:01:39,958
the Mach 5 sprouts
special grip tires

24
00:01:40,041 --> 00:01:43,833
for traction over
any kind of terrain.

25
00:01:43,916 --> 00:01:46,291
Control C releases
powerful rotary saws

26
00:01:46,375 --> 00:01:47,416
from the front of the car

27
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,833
to slice through any
and all obstacles.

28
00:01:49,916 --> 00:01:52,625
D: When pressed, this button
releases a powerful deflector

29
00:01:52,708 --> 00:01:53,958
which seals the cockpit into

30
00:01:54,041 --> 00:01:56,208
a bullet and crash-proof
and watertight chamber.

31
00:01:56,291 --> 00:01:58,958
E is the control for
special illumination,

32
00:01:59,041 --> 00:02:01,166
which enables me to see
further and more clearly

33
00:02:01,250 --> 00:02:02,791
than with ordinary headlights.

34
00:02:02,875 --> 00:02:04,125
When I'm in a dangerous place,

35
00:02:04,208 --> 00:02:06,458
I can traverse these lights
singly or in tandem.

36
00:02:06,541 --> 00:02:09,833
F is the control I use when
the Mach 5 is underwater.

37
00:02:09,916 --> 00:02:11,375
The cockpit is
supplied with oxygen,

38
00:02:11,458 --> 00:02:14,041
and then a periscope is
raised to scan the surface.

39
00:02:14,125 --> 00:02:15,791
Everything that it sees
is relayed down to me

40
00:02:15,875 --> 00:02:17,166
by television.

41
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:19,250
Control G releases
a homing robot,

42
00:02:19,333 --> 00:02:21,708
which can carry pictures
or tape-recorded messages

43
00:02:21,791 --> 00:02:24,500
to whomever and wherever
I wanna send them.

44
00:02:24,583 --> 00:02:26,166
With this car that Pops built,

45
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:28,208
the most fabulous
car ever driven,

46
00:02:28,291 --> 00:02:31,458
I've been competing in auto
races throughout the world.

47
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:42,500
[engine revving]

48
00:02:45,875 --> 00:02:47,666
I love taking the wheel!

49
00:02:53,916 --> 00:02:55,250
[SPEED]
Take it easy, Trixie.

50
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:56,541
The speed limit through
here's only 80 miles an hour.

51
00:02:56,625 --> 00:02:57,791
Huh? Oh!

52
00:02:57,875 --> 00:03:00,416
I didn't realize we were
going twice that fast.

53
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:01,875
It drives so beautifully.

54
00:03:01,958 --> 00:03:02,750
I know that.

55
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:04,291
But we've got to obey the law.

56
00:03:04,375 --> 00:03:05,458
Huh?

57
00:03:05,541 --> 00:03:07,666
Looks like a reckless
driver back there.

58
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:09,041
[gasps]

59
00:03:13,916 --> 00:03:14,958
[whistles]

60
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:16,125
Watch where you're driving!

61
00:03:16,208 --> 00:03:18,666
You drive just like a girl!

62
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:19,708
Did you hear that?!

63
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:21,000
[SPEED]
Forget it!

64
00:03:22,833 --> 00:03:24,416
[BOY A] What's the matter?
We hurt your feelings?

65
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:25,791
[BOY B]
Wah, now we got her mad.

66
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:27,791
[SPEED]
Hey, take it easy.

67
00:03:31,125 --> 00:03:33,041
[BOYS heckling]

68
00:03:33,125 --> 00:03:34,750
--[TRIXIE gasps]
--[SPEED] Careful!

69
00:03:36,875 --> 00:03:38,333
--[BOY A] Let's do it again!
--[BOY C] Hang on!

70
00:03:38,416 --> 00:03:40,000
[BOYS laughing]

71
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:40,833
[SPEED]
Cut that out!

72
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:41,833
You want us to crash?!

73
00:03:41,916 --> 00:03:43,916
[BOYS laughing]

74
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,625
[tires screech]

75
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:50,833
[SPEED]
Look out!

76
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:52,708
[BOTH gasp]

77
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:04,375
[tires screech]

78
00:04:04,458 --> 00:04:05,666
[SPEED sighs]

79
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:08,125
We almost got it.

80
00:04:08,208 --> 00:04:10,500
Ooh! That was a close call!

81
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:11,791
[BOTH gasp]

82
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:13,291
[BOTH gasp]

83
00:04:14,375 --> 00:04:17,000
[BOY A] Hey! What's the
idea of botherin' us?!

84
00:04:17,083 --> 00:04:18,208
Think you're a wise guy?

85
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:19,458
Come outta there!

86
00:04:19,541 --> 00:04:21,250
We didn't start
trouble, you did!

87
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:24,291
Hey! Quiet, girlie!
You keep out of it!

88
00:04:24,375 --> 00:04:26,708
[SPRITLE gasps]
This doesn't look good.

89
00:04:26,791 --> 00:04:28,708
You better drive away
while you can.

90
00:04:28,791 --> 00:04:31,375
Oh, yeah? Come on, boys,
let's smash his car up.

91
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:32,791
Wait a minute!

92
00:04:32,875 --> 00:04:34,666
There's a whole buncha buttons
on his steering column.

93
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:37,208
This car must be the Mach 5.

94
00:04:37,291 --> 00:04:39,250
You're right.
It does look like it!

95
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:41,166
And he's gotta be the
best racer in the world,

96
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:42,958
our hero, Speed Racer!

97
00:04:43,041 --> 00:04:44,500
Could I have your
autograph, Speed?

98
00:04:44,583 --> 00:04:45,958
Sign my book!

99
00:04:46,041 --> 00:04:48,166
How 'bout autographin' my shirt?

100
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:50,833
Well, they changed their minds
pretty fast, didn't they?

101
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:52,041
[SPRITLE laughs]

102
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:54,750
My brother Speed's very popular.

103
00:04:56,041 --> 00:04:58,000
[SPEED] A racer shouldn't
drive recklessly.

104
00:04:58,083 --> 00:04:59,500
Making a corner, for instance.

105
00:04:59,583 --> 00:05:02,083
You must slow down before it
and then speed up around it.

106
00:05:02,166 --> 00:05:03,791
That means shifting down
at a certain point,

107
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:06,291
and then accelerating
for maximum traction.

108
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:07,625
It's gotta be done right.

109
00:05:07,708 --> 00:05:09,708
Make just one mistake,
and it'll take a long time

110
00:05:09,791 --> 00:05:11,083
until you're able to catch up.

111
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:12,375
And you can lose
control of your car,

112
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:13,625
which can be very dangerous.

113
00:05:13,708 --> 00:05:15,000
[THUG A]
A regular wise guy.

114
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:17,708
You like showin' off for
those kids, don't cha, kid?

115
00:05:17,791 --> 00:05:19,416
I was talking to my
friends here and not to you.

116
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,916
So keep out of it,
why don't you?

117
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,083
[THUG A]
Why should I?

118
00:05:22,166 --> 00:05:23,625
I used to be a
professional racer myself.

119
00:05:23,708 --> 00:05:26,083
But I don't have as
big a mouth as you, kid.

120
00:05:26,166 --> 00:05:27,541
[BOY A]
Hey, you!

121
00:05:27,625 --> 00:05:29,208
Get your hands off
my friend, Speed!

122
00:05:29,291 --> 00:05:31,583
You keep out of this, squirt.

123
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:32,833
[BOYS groan]

124
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:33,625
[SPEED]
That wasn't nice.

125
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:35,041
Ow! Ow! Ow!

126
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:36,625
[SPEED] I was just giving them
some tips about driving.

127
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:37,625
Hey!

128
00:05:37,708 --> 00:05:39,458
--[SPEED gasps]
--[THUG A groans]

129
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,916
[gasps]

130
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,291
[THUG C] Why don't you fight
instead of throwing things?

131
00:05:43,375 --> 00:05:44,541
Get to work!

132
00:05:44,625 --> 00:05:46,333
[THUG B]
Yeah! Um, good idea!

133
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:47,458
Hey, now, wait a minute.

134
00:05:47,541 --> 00:05:49,166
There's no need for
any more trouble.

135
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:50,291
[THUG B yells]

136
00:05:50,375 --> 00:05:54,958
--[SPEED grunting]
--[THUG B groaning]

137
00:05:55,041 --> 00:05:58,541
--[SPEED grunting]
--[THUG C groaning]

138
00:05:58,625 --> 00:05:59,916
Had enough? Or would
you like some more?

139
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,333
[THUG C]
No! No more!

140
00:06:01,416 --> 00:06:02,250
[THUG A]
Let's get outta here!

141
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,333
[THUG B]
Run for your life!

142
00:06:03,416 --> 00:06:04,375
[ALL laugh]

143
00:06:04,458 --> 00:06:06,583
[BOY B]
Hurray, Speed! Hurray!

144
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:07,791
You're a groovy fighter!

145
00:06:07,875 --> 00:06:09,416
Tell us a racing story!

146
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:12,166
Is racing the only thing Speed
likes to talk about? Hm?!

147
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,958
[SPEED] Once I raced against
the trickiest team in the world.

148
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,541
They were called the
Car Acrobatic Team.

149
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,250
[BOY B]
Wow! Were they really acrobats?

150
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:18,291
[SPEED]
No, but their cars were.

151
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:19,666
[BOY C]
What could they do?

152
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:20,833
[SPRITLE]
And that's not all.

153
00:06:20,916 --> 00:06:23,333
The Mach 5 can
even run underwater!

154
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:25,791
It can be a submarine
as well as an aeroplane?

155
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:27,375
--[TRIXIE] Spritle!
--[GIRL gasps]

156
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:29,875
Don't expect people to believe
the Mach 5 can do everything.

157
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:31,875
I didn't lie,
and she believes it!

158
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:33,291
Hi, my name is Janine.

159
00:06:33,375 --> 00:06:35,083
This is a fabulous car.

160
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:36,750
I'm Trixie. I'm glad
you like the car.

161
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:38,083
Would you like
to go for a drive?

162
00:06:38,166 --> 00:06:39,125
Do you mean it?

163
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:41,125
I sure would!

164
00:06:41,208 --> 00:06:42,333
According to this speedometer,

165
00:06:42,416 --> 00:06:45,041
this must be the
fastest car in the world!

166
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:46,958
You like the Mach 5, I guess.

167
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:48,833
Uh-huh. I wanna be a racer.

168
00:06:48,916 --> 00:06:50,458
But I suppose I'll
never be able to be one

169
00:06:50,541 --> 00:06:52,500
because my father hates cars.

170
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:54,625
I'm sorry to hear it.

171
00:06:54,708 --> 00:06:57,625
[engine revs]

172
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:59,291
It goes fast,
just remember that.

173
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:00,541
[JANINE]
I will!

174
00:07:05,250 --> 00:07:06,416
--[MAN gasps]
--[JANINE gasps]

175
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,375
[tires screech]

176
00:07:08,458 --> 00:07:11,333
[MAN]
Down, Boy! Easy!

177
00:07:11,416 --> 00:07:13,708
--Do something!
--[SPEED] Trixie!

178
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:16,625
[SPEED]
Whoa! Whoa, boy! Whoa!

179
00:07:16,708 --> 00:07:18,666
[MAN groans]

180
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,583
[SPEED] Sir, are you all right?
Are you all right?!

181
00:07:20,666 --> 00:07:22,458
[JANINE]
Oh, Papa!

182
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:24,958
Janine, were you
driving that car?

183
00:07:25,041 --> 00:07:26,958
I was. I'm sorry, Papa.

184
00:07:27,041 --> 00:07:29,541
[MAN] After I forbade
you to drive a car?!

185
00:07:29,625 --> 00:07:31,291
I'll smash it into
a pile of junk!

186
00:07:31,375 --> 00:07:33,208
[JANINE]
No, Papa! Don't touch it!

187
00:07:33,291 --> 00:07:34,958
[groans]

188
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:36,208
[MAN grunting]

189
00:07:36,291 --> 00:07:37,583
[JANINE]
No!

190
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:40,583
It doesn't belong to me!

191
00:07:40,666 --> 00:07:42,958
I don't care. I'll smash it
because you were driving it.

192
00:07:43,041 --> 00:07:45,458
No! You have no right
to smash it up like that!

193
00:07:45,541 --> 00:07:46,500
Janine, get away!

194
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:48,041
--[SPEED] Hold it!
--[MAN] Huh?

195
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:49,916
I'm warning you. You'd better
not hit your daughter again.

196
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:50,958
[MAN]
I'm sorry.

197
00:07:51,041 --> 00:07:52,375
I've been too upset
even to think.

198
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:54,791
He gets this way whenever
he thinks of cars!

199
00:07:54,875 --> 00:07:56,833
All cars are weapons on wheels.

200
00:07:56,916 --> 00:07:58,083
I hate them!

201
00:07:58,166 --> 00:08:00,000
They should be destroyed,
every one of them.

202
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:02,666
When they're driven right,
they're perfectly safe, sir!

203
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,208
You don't understand!

204
00:08:04,291 --> 00:08:08,333
Don't tell me about cars!
I lost my son in a car accident!

205
00:08:08,416 --> 00:08:11,708
I have the best reason in
the world for hating cars.

206
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:14,333
[SPEED]
Sorry, I didn't know that, sir.

207
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:17,000
You remind me of my son--
the one that I lost.

208
00:08:17,083 --> 00:08:19,916
Now I understand why
you acted the way you did.

209
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,291
I just couldn't help it.

210
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:22,500
Tell me about yourself.

211
00:08:22,583 --> 00:08:23,666
Are you a student?

212
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:25,833
I used to be. Now I'm
a racing-- Oop!

213
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:27,250
[TRIXIE gasps]

214
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,625
[SPEED] I mean, now I'm working
at my father's factory.

215
00:08:29,708 --> 00:08:30,333
[sighs]

216
00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:31,583
[MAN]
Is that so?

217
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:33,333
Well, good luck, my boy.

218
00:08:33,416 --> 00:08:34,791
Goodbye.

219
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:39,125
Janine! I want you to
come home. Right now!

220
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:46,416
Well...! Hmph.

221
00:08:48,041 --> 00:08:50,541
[POPS] The paint was
scraped completely off.

222
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:53,333
But another car usually
causes more damage than this.

223
00:08:53,416 --> 00:08:54,541
You've gotta be careful, Speed.

224
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:56,500
There are so many cars
on the roads today.

225
00:08:56,583 --> 00:08:58,500
Okay, but I'm a good driver.

226
00:08:58,583 --> 00:08:59,791
[SPARKY]
But a lot of drivers aren't.

227
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:01,291
And they're the ones
you have to look out for.

228
00:09:01,375 --> 00:09:02,375
Listen to who's talking.

229
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:03,708
How old are you, Sparky?

230
00:09:03,791 --> 00:09:05,166
[SPARKY]
Hm?

231
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,583
[ALL laugh]

232
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:10,416
[POPS gasps]
It's no laughing matter.

233
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:13,500
I read about accidents
in the paper every day!

234
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:18,125
More accidents. There are
some in the paper every day.

235
00:09:18,208 --> 00:09:23,250
Ugh. We wouldn't have them
if we didn't have cars.

236
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:26,208
Janine, I don't want to catch
you around a car again.

237
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:27,833
I'll be right back, Papa.

238
00:09:27,916 --> 00:09:28,791
[MAN]
Janine!

239
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:30,250
Where are you going?

240
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:32,375
Hm...

241
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:34,625
"New racing car
track opens today.

242
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:36,541
Well-known drivers
are to complete."

243
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:37,833
Hm...

244
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:50,750
[tires screech]

245
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:51,916
How's the track?

246
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,125
It's one of the best
I've ever driven on.

247
00:09:54,208 --> 00:09:56,750
There's a terrific S-curve
and a hairpin turn.

248
00:09:56,833 --> 00:09:58,875
Twenty more laps and you'll
be used to it, Speed.

249
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:00,375
[JANINE]
Oh, hello, Speed.

250
00:10:00,458 --> 00:10:01,791
[SPEED]
Hi, Janine.

251
00:10:01,875 --> 00:10:03,708
I read about the new track
and figured you'd be here.

252
00:10:03,791 --> 00:10:04,833
Won't your father be angry

253
00:10:04,916 --> 00:10:06,583
if he finds you came
out to the track?

254
00:10:06,666 --> 00:10:08,791
I can't help it.
I've just got to drive fast.

255
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:10,500
[SPARKY] Go ahead, Speed.
Switch on the ignition.

256
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:12,041
[SPEED]
Okle-dokle!

257
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:18,083
It's fine now.

258
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:19,041
Huh?

259
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:20,583
What's comin' down the track?

260
00:10:21,666 --> 00:10:23,041
[hooves clacking]

261
00:10:23,125 --> 00:10:24,625
It's Papa!

262
00:10:27,708 --> 00:10:30,250
[PEOPLE chattering]

263
00:10:31,583 --> 00:10:34,083
--Janine! Easy. What did I say?!
--[horse neighs]

264
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:36,583
Didn't I forbid you to go near
any more cars? You did!

265
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:38,291
Now wait just a minute!

266
00:10:38,375 --> 00:10:39,750
Don't interfere again!

267
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:41,583
I invited your daughter
to come out to the track.

268
00:10:41,666 --> 00:10:43,625
It's my fault that she's here!

269
00:10:43,708 --> 00:10:45,333
You're really a
professional racer!

270
00:10:45,416 --> 00:10:46,791
Liar!

271
00:10:46,875 --> 00:10:47,500
[gasps]

272
00:10:47,583 --> 00:10:48,500
Leave him alone, Papa!

273
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:49,791
[MAN]
Get away!

274
00:10:51,291 --> 00:10:53,708
They shouldn't build race
tracks for racing cars.

275
00:10:53,791 --> 00:10:55,166
Here come the cars.

276
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:56,625
You'd better get out of the way.

277
00:10:56,708 --> 00:10:58,000
[JANINE]
Papa!

278
00:11:22,791 --> 00:11:24,375
[DRIVER A screams]

279
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:28,000
Hey!

280
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:32,125
[tires screech]

281
00:11:33,166 --> 00:11:35,125
[DRIVER B screams]

282
00:11:37,041 --> 00:11:39,166
Whoa!

283
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:42,791
[MAN] There... That gets
rid of some cars.

284
00:11:42,875 --> 00:11:45,625
Papa... He should never
have gone out there. [sobs]

285
00:11:45,708 --> 00:11:47,041
A catastrophe...

286
00:11:47,125 --> 00:11:49,375
I'll make sure you pay
for what you've done!

287
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:52,750
It wasn't my fault the
horse got in their way!

288
00:11:52,833 --> 00:11:54,333
[OFFICIAL A]
Come back here!

289
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:57,958
[THUG A grunts]

290
00:11:58,041 --> 00:11:59,375
[OFFICIAL A groans]

291
00:11:59,458 --> 00:12:01,833
We'll be glad to take care
of the rest of 'em, sir.

292
00:12:01,916 --> 00:12:03,625
Just who are you men, anyway?

293
00:12:03,708 --> 00:12:06,333
Just three friendly fellows
who don't like cars either.

294
00:12:06,416 --> 00:12:08,875
I can use men like you.
Come to see me later.

295
00:12:10,291 --> 00:12:11,583
[THUGS chuckling]

296
00:12:11,666 --> 00:12:13,125
Looks like we found a sucker.

297
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:16,458
[THUGS chuckling]

298
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:19,833
[tires screeching]

299
00:12:19,916 --> 00:12:23,250
[cars honking]

300
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:25,083
Out of the way! I'm in a hurry!

301
00:12:25,166 --> 00:12:27,250
This isn't a horse race track!

302
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:30,750
Listen, stop driving cars.
They're much too dangerous!

303
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:32,333
Out of my way, go on!

304
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:34,416
Can't you understand that
cars are rolling weapons?!

305
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,750
You're a nut and I'm
gonna give you a crack!

306
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:38,583
[groans]

307
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:39,750
[MAN]
Giddy-up!

308
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:53,250
[MAN] So there's only
one thing for us to do.

309
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:55,875
We must show people
how dangerous cars are.

310
00:12:55,958 --> 00:12:57,416
[snickers]

311
00:12:57,500 --> 00:13:00,583
That should be a cinch
for guys like us. Right?

312
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:01,708
[chuckles]

313
00:13:01,791 --> 00:13:04,875
As long as we get
lots of loot for it.

314
00:13:04,958 --> 00:13:06,791
[MAN] How about this
for a down payment?

315
00:13:06,875 --> 00:13:07,791
[THUGS]
Look at that!

316
00:13:07,875 --> 00:13:09,125
Gimme!

317
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:14,291
[THUGS grumbling]

318
00:13:14,375 --> 00:13:16,125
You must never tell
anybody that I'm the one

319
00:13:16,208 --> 00:13:17,500
behind this whole thing.

320
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:19,458
We won't, Mr. Trotter.
Word of honor.

321
00:13:19,541 --> 00:13:21,000
--[THUGS snicker]
--[phone rings]

322
00:13:21,083 --> 00:13:23,125
[THUGS gasp]

323
00:13:23,208 --> 00:13:24,500
[JANINE]
Papa, it's Janine.

324
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:26,500
Janine! Where are you?
Where are you calling from?!

325
00:13:26,583 --> 00:13:28,041
[JANINE]
Never mind.

326
00:13:28,125 --> 00:13:30,666
Unless you change your mind
about cars, I won't come home!

327
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:31,875
Janine! Janine!

328
00:13:31,958 --> 00:13:33,166
Operator! Operator!

329
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,833
What is it? Anything wrong
with the telephone?

330
00:13:34,916 --> 00:13:36,833
--[TROTTER] Quiet!
--[THUGS yelp]

331
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:38,833
Just follow my orders
and get to work!

332
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:39,666
Or else!

333
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:42,083
[THUGS yelping]

334
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:43,916
Don't worry; we'll earn it!

335
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,000
What are we going to do?

336
00:13:45,083 --> 00:13:47,041
[TRIXIE]
Do you have any ideas, Janine?

337
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:48,458
My father's so stubborn,

338
00:13:48,541 --> 00:13:50,541
it's almost impossible to get
him to change his mind.

339
00:13:50,625 --> 00:13:51,500
[sobs]

340
00:13:51,583 --> 00:13:52,666
He was very upset.

341
00:13:52,750 --> 00:13:53,750
Maybe if we leave him
alone for a while,

342
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,333
he'll calm down a bit.

343
00:13:55,416 --> 00:13:58,041
And maybe it'd be better if you
stayed here for a while, Janine.

344
00:13:58,125 --> 00:14:00,125
Oh, thank you. I will.

345
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:23,583
[THUG C]
You finished?

346
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:24,958
[THUG A]
Is that car all set to crash?

347
00:14:25,041 --> 00:14:27,375
[THUG B] Yeah. Just wait'll
tomorrow, eh, boys?

348
00:14:27,458 --> 00:14:32,083
[THUGS snicker]

349
00:14:32,166 --> 00:14:35,875
[engine revs]

350
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:44,833
--[screams]
--[tires screech]

351
00:14:44,916 --> 00:14:47,500
--[screams]
--[tires screech]

352
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:51,208
[PEOPLE screaming]

353
00:14:51,291 --> 00:14:54,083
[cars honking]

354
00:14:54,166 --> 00:14:55,333
That's just the beginning.

355
00:14:55,416 --> 00:14:59,750
[THUGS laugh]

356
00:15:02,541 --> 00:15:05,583
[THUGS laughing]

357
00:15:18,041 --> 00:15:20,083
[THUGS laughing]

358
00:15:23,875 --> 00:15:25,750
[POLICE A]
Halt! Stop! Stop!

359
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:28,250
Sorry, son, you can't
go into the city today.

360
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:31,333
We're having a tremendous
amount of accidents.

361
00:15:31,416 --> 00:15:33,416
And because of the tremendous
amount of accidents,

362
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:36,750
metropolitan traffic has
been hopelessly snarled.

363
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:37,791
[JANINE]
What do you think's causing

364
00:15:37,875 --> 00:15:38,875
all the accidents, Speed?

365
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:40,375
I haven't the vaguest idea!

366
00:15:40,458 --> 00:15:42,291
[BARTENDER]
Well, I have a theory.

367
00:15:42,375 --> 00:15:44,208
I figure the accidents
aren't accidental.

368
00:15:44,291 --> 00:15:45,625
Somebody's causing them?

369
00:15:45,708 --> 00:15:46,958
[TROTTER]
There!

370
00:15:47,041 --> 00:15:49,750
Now, the next job's at
Pop Racer's motor factory.

371
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:51,125
[THUGS chuckling]

372
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:53,541
You want us to take care
of Speed Racer, eh?

373
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:55,875
But be careful that
the police don't get wise.

374
00:15:55,958 --> 00:15:58,416
Heh, don't worry.
The cops'll never catch us.

375
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,500
[chuckles]

376
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:13,833
I just saw three strange men
running into the factory!

377
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:14,708
Robbers, I guess.

378
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:15,375
Let's go after them.

379
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:15,958
[SPARKY]
Okay.

380
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:16,916
I'm all ready!

381
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,583
My arms are aching for action.

382
00:16:18,666 --> 00:16:21,166
[CHIM CHIM gibbers]

383
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:24,500
[THUG A grunts, groans]

384
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:25,791
I'll bet you're the guys

385
00:16:25,875 --> 00:16:27,500
who've been causing
those terrible accidents!

386
00:16:27,583 --> 00:16:28,541
So what if we are?

387
00:16:28,625 --> 00:16:29,750
What are you gonna do about it?

388
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:30,625
C'mere, sonny.

389
00:16:30,708 --> 00:16:31,833
[SPARKY]
Give yourselves up!

390
00:16:31,916 --> 00:16:33,875
You're not gonna be able
to get away from us.

391
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:35,375
That's what you think.
Get 'em, boys.

392
00:16:35,458 --> 00:16:36,166
[SPEED grunts]

393
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:38,083
[THUG A groans]

394
00:16:38,166 --> 00:16:39,625
[THUG B groans]

395
00:16:39,708 --> 00:16:42,291
--[SPEED grunting]
--[THUG A groaning]

396
00:16:44,208 --> 00:16:46,958
--[SPEED grunting]
--[THUG C groaning]

397
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:51,208
[THUB B grunts, groans]

398
00:16:51,291 --> 00:16:52,708
Don't get them all so fast!

399
00:16:52,791 --> 00:16:54,791
Save one of them for me!

400
00:16:54,875 --> 00:16:55,541
[gasps]

401
00:16:55,625 --> 00:16:57,541
[SPRITLE laughs]

402
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:00,375
[SPEED] Why did you fix
those cars so they'd crash?!

403
00:17:00,458 --> 00:17:01,833
Answer me!

404
00:17:01,916 --> 00:17:04,125
Mr. Trotter paid us to fix
those cars so they'd crash.

405
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:06,666
What?! You were paid
by Janine's father?!

406
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:09,291
[THUG C groans]

407
00:17:09,375 --> 00:17:10,416
[TROTTER]
You!

408
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,791
What's the meaning of this?!

409
00:17:11,875 --> 00:17:13,000
There's no use
lying, Mr. Trotter.

410
00:17:13,083 --> 00:17:14,708
This man's already
confessed to the crime.

411
00:17:14,791 --> 00:17:15,958
I don't know what
you're talking about.

412
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:17,500
Get out of here! Go home!

413
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:18,791
Leave me alone!

414
00:17:18,875 --> 00:17:20,041
If you were any
kind of decent man,

415
00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:21,875
you'd go to the
police and tell them.

416
00:17:21,958 --> 00:17:23,208
Get out, I said!

417
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:25,416
But before you do,
tell me where my daughter is.

418
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:26,750
Where is she hiding?

419
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,250
Janine is with
Trixie in a new car,

420
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:30,375
and they're driving toward
the Craggy Peak Mountains.

421
00:17:30,458 --> 00:17:32,500
Mr. Trotter, I fixed
the brakes on that car.

422
00:17:32,583 --> 00:17:33,958
Just as you ordered me to, sir.

423
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:34,958
My daughter's in danger.

424
00:17:35,041 --> 00:17:36,125
[SPEED groans]

425
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:40,833
[TROTTER]
Giddy-up!

426
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:46,958
Better hurry, Speed!

427
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:54,208
[gasps]

428
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:55,333
The brakes aren't working!

429
00:17:55,416 --> 00:17:56,375
[JANINE gasps]

430
00:18:07,416 --> 00:18:08,625
Now it's impossible to stop.

431
00:18:08,708 --> 00:18:10,208
Try the emergency brake!

432
00:18:15,916 --> 00:18:17,625
We're going even faster now!

433
00:18:23,125 --> 00:18:24,208
[TROTTER]
Whoa!

434
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:28,083
Come on. Hop in my car.

435
00:18:28,166 --> 00:18:29,750
It's the only way you'll
catch up to your daughter.

436
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:30,750
[TROTTER grunts]

437
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:32,000
You'll never catch
her like that.

438
00:18:32,083 --> 00:18:33,083
Come on!

439
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:35,500
[screams]

440
00:18:42,708 --> 00:18:45,000
[screams]

441
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:48,000
I swore never to ride in a car.

442
00:18:48,083 --> 00:18:49,208
Giddy-up!

443
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:52,791
Okay!

444
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:11,875
--[BOTH scream]
--[tires screech]

445
00:19:14,791 --> 00:19:15,916
[gasps]

446
00:19:20,083 --> 00:19:22,291
[TRIXIE gasps, grunts]

447
00:19:22,375 --> 00:19:23,541
[tires screeching]

448
00:19:23,625 --> 00:19:25,625
[TRIXIE] Something's wrong
with the steering!

449
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:31,541
[BOTH scream]

450
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,708
[gasps]

451
00:19:41,791 --> 00:19:45,083
[tires screech]

452
00:19:45,166 --> 00:19:46,458
[SPEED]
Trixie!

453
00:19:47,875 --> 00:19:49,708
Speed, help Janine!

454
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:51,083
[SPEED]
Hm?

455
00:19:51,166 --> 00:19:52,958
[gasps]

456
00:19:53,041 --> 00:19:55,125
Janine! Janine!

457
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:57,375
[TROTTER]
Wait!

458
00:20:01,125 --> 00:20:02,625
[TROTTER]
Give her to me.

459
00:20:02,708 --> 00:20:04,583
I'll take my daughter
to a hospital.

460
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:05,750
[horse neighs]

461
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:08,583
[TROTTER]
Whoa! Easy, boy, easy!

462
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:12,958
Whoa! Come on,
take it easy! Hey!

463
00:20:13,041 --> 00:20:15,916
What's the matter with you?
Come on, let's go!

464
00:20:17,125 --> 00:20:18,250
Listen, Mr. Trotter.

465
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:19,750
Your daughter needs
medical help right away.

466
00:20:19,833 --> 00:20:22,583
And that horse'll never get
her to the hospital in time!

467
00:20:22,666 --> 00:20:24,375
[TRIXIE] We don't care
how you feel about cars.

468
00:20:24,458 --> 00:20:26,833
Janine is more important!

469
00:20:26,916 --> 00:20:28,333
[SPEED grunts]

470
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:29,791
[TRIXIE]
Hurry, Speed!

471
00:21:01,625 --> 00:21:04,166
[JANINE] Oh, thank you.
Thank you all for everything!

472
00:21:04,250 --> 00:21:05,625
[POPS]
Chim Chim!

473
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:09,291
--[JANINE giggles]
--[door clicks]

474
00:21:09,375 --> 00:21:11,083
[gasps]

475
00:21:11,166 --> 00:21:12,625
--Papa!
--My daughter!

476
00:21:12,708 --> 00:21:16,041
[JANINE] Oh, Papa! Why didn't
you come to visit me sooner?

477
00:21:16,125 --> 00:21:18,875
I've been in jail, paying for
the crimes I've committed.

478
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:21,000
It wasn't until today
that they released me.

479
00:21:21,083 --> 00:21:23,666
Promise you'll never do
anything like that again.

480
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:25,083
[TROTTER]
I promise, Janine.

481
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:27,291
I've learned my lesson.

482
00:21:27,375 --> 00:21:28,625
Oh, let's forget it.

483
00:21:28,708 --> 00:21:30,458
It's time you were
both going home.

484
00:21:30,541 --> 00:21:32,375
I have a present
for you, Mr. Trotter--

485
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:34,250
a sports car I built
with my own hands.

486
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:37,458
It'll never get tired, and it
runs even better than a horse.

487
00:21:37,541 --> 00:21:38,708
[TROTTER]
Thanks, Mr. Racer.

488
00:21:38,791 --> 00:21:40,791
I realize now that a car
can be either a weapon

489
00:21:40,875 --> 00:21:44,166
or a lifesaver. It all
depends on who's driving it.

490
00:21:47,083 --> 00:21:52,083
[whistle blows]

491
00:21:52,166 --> 00:21:54,333
Shall I carry you across
the street, old lady?

492
00:21:54,416 --> 00:21:55,541
Hang on.

493
00:21:55,625 --> 00:21:56,583
Thanks, young man.

494
00:21:56,666 --> 00:21:57,791
[THUG A chuckles]

495
00:21:57,875 --> 00:21:59,708
Okay, whoever's next,
just hop on my back.

496
00:21:59,791 --> 00:22:00,833
[dog barks]

497
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:06,125
[TROTTER] I gave them
orders that, from now on,

498
00:22:06,208 --> 00:22:08,166
they'd better help
whomever they can.

499
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:09,875
Very good idea.

500
00:22:09,958 --> 00:22:11,791
Janine, I'm going to let
you be a racing driver.

501
00:22:11,875 --> 00:22:12,583
Thanks, Papa.

502
00:22:12,666 --> 00:22:13,750
That's great!

503
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:15,458
Speed'll give you
racing driver lessons.

504
00:22:15,541 --> 00:22:17,500
And you'd better pay
very close attention.

505
00:22:17,583 --> 00:22:18,833
I shall.

506
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:22,541
[whistle blows]

507
00:22:22,625 --> 00:22:26,500
